question: Which organizations are mentioned in articles published after 2020?
cypher: MATCH (a:Article)-[:MENTIONS]->(o:Organization) WHERE a.date > date("2020-01-01") RETURN DISTINCT o
typeql: match $a isa article; $o isa organization; (article: $a, organization: $o) isa mentions; fetch { "o": $o };
review_reason: Missing date filter: TypeQL does not filter articles by date > 2020-01-01 as required

question: What are the names of organizations that have at least one investor but no subsidiaries?
cypher: MATCH (o:Organization) WHERE exists((o)<-[:HAS_INVESTOR]-()) AND NOT exists((o)-[:HAS_SUBSIDIARY]->()) RETURN o.name
typeql: match $o isa organization; fetch { "name": $o.name };
review_reason: Missing investor and subsidiary logic: TypeQL returns all organizations, not just those with investors and without subsidiaries

question: Which organizations are both suppliers and competitors to other organizations?
cypher: MATCH (o1:Organization)-[:HAS_SUPPLIER]->(o2:Organization) WHERE (o1)-[:HAS_COMPETITOR]->(o2) RETURN o1.name AS org1, o2.name AS org2
typeql: match $o1 isa organization; $o2 isa organization; (customer: $o1, supplier: $o2) isa supplies; fetch { "org1": $o1.name, "org2": $o2.name };
review_reason: Missing competitor condition: TypeQL only checks supplier relationship, not the additional competitor relationship between same orgs

question: Which articles mention organizations with a revenue less than 10 million?
cypher: MATCH (a:Article)-[:MENTIONS]->(o:Organization) WHERE o.revenue < 1E7 RETURN a, o
typeql: match $a isa article; $o isa organization; (article: $a, organization: $o) isa mentions; $o has revenue $o_revenue; $o_revenue < 1; fetch { "a": $a, "o": $o };
review_reason: Wrong revenue threshold: TypeQL uses < 1 instead of < 10000000 (10 million)

question: List the organizations that have their CEOs also serving as board members in other organizations.
cypher: MATCH (o:Organization)-[:HAS_CEO]->(ceo:Person) WHERE EXISTS { (ceo)-[:HAS_BOARD_MEMBER]-(:Organization) } RETURN o.name AS organization, ceo.name AS ceo
typeql: match $o isa organization; $ceo isa person; (organization: $o, ceo: $ceo) isa ceo_of; fetch { "organization": $o.name, "ceo": $ceo.name };
review_reason: Missing board member check: TypeQL does not verify that the CEO is also a board member in other organizations

question: Name the children of 'Julie Spellman Sweet'.
cypher: MATCH (p:Person {name: 'Julie Spellman Sweet'})-[:HAS_CHILD]->(child:Person) RETURN child.name
typeql: match $p isa person, has name "Julie Spellman Sweet"; $child isa person; fetch { "name": $child.name };
review_reason: Missing parent-child relationship: TypeQL matches person Julie and any child separately but does not connect them with the parent_of relation

question: Which organizations are based in cities not in the 'United States of America'?
cypher: MATCH (o:Organization)-[:IN_CITY]->(c:City)-[:IN_COUNTRY]->(country:Country) WHERE country.name <> 'United States of America' RETURN o.name AS organization, c.name AS city, country.name AS country
typeql: match $o isa organization; $c isa city; $country isa country; (organization: $o, city: $c) isa located_in; fetch { "organization": $o.name, "city": $c.city_name, "country": $country.country_name };
review_reason: Missing country filter and city-country relation: TypeQL does not filter by non-USA countries and does not join city to country

question: Identify organizations that have more than 3 board members.
cypher: MATCH (o:Organization) WHERE size([(o)-[:HAS_BOARD_MEMBER]->(:Person) | 1]) > 3 RETURN o
typeql: match $o isa organization; fetch { "o": $o };
review_reason: Missing board member count condition: TypeQL returns all organizations without filtering by board member count > 3

question: What are the names of organizations that have both public and private subsidiaries?
cypher: MATCH (o:Organization) WHERE EXISTS { (o)-[:HAS_SUBSIDIARY]->(:Organization {isPublic: true}) } AND EXISTS { (o)-[:HAS_SUBSIDIARY]->(:Organization {isPublic: false}) } RETURN o.name
typeql: match $o isa organization; fetch { "name": $o.name };
review_reason: Missing subsidiary and public/private checks: TypeQL returns all organizations without checking for both public and private subsidiaries

question: Which persons are investors in organizations that have a revenue over 100 million?
cypher: MATCH (p:Person)-[:HAS_INVESTOR]->(o:Organization) WHERE o.revenue > 1E8 RETURN p.name AS investor, o.name AS organization, o.revenue AS revenue
typeql: match $p isa person; $o isa organization; (investor: $p, organization: $o) isa invested_in; $o has revenue $o_revenue; $o_revenue > 1; fetch { "investor": $p.name, "organization": $o.name, "revenue": $o.revenue };
review_reason: Wrong revenue threshold: TypeQL uses > 1 instead of > 100000000 (100 million)

question: What is the revenue of the subsidiaries of 'Accenture'?
cypher: MATCH (accenture:Organization {name: 'Accenture'})-[:HAS_SUBSIDIARY*]->(subsidiary:Organization) WHERE subsidiary.revenue IS NOT NULL RETURN subsidiary.name AS subsidiary, subsidiary.revenue AS revenue
typeql: match $accenture isa organization, has name "Accenture"; $subsidiary isa organization; $subsidiary has revenue $subsidiary_revenue; fetch { "subsidiary": $subsidiary.name, "revenue": $subsidiary.revenue };
review_reason: Missing subsidiary relationship: TypeQL matches any organization with revenue, not specifically subsidiaries of Accenture

question: Which organizations have a CEO who has written an article?
cypher: MATCH (o:Organization)-[:HAS_CEO]->(ceo:Person)<-[:AUTHOR]-(a:Article) RETURN o.name AS organization, ceo.name AS ceo, a.title AS article
typeql: match $o isa organization; $ceo isa person; $a isa article; (organization: $o, ceo: $ceo) isa ceo_of; fetch { "organization": $o.name, "ceo": $ceo.name, "article": $a.title };
review_reason: Missing author relationship: TypeQL does not connect CEO to article via authorship

question: What are the names of organizations that have been competitors for more than 10 years?
cypher: MATCH (o1:Organization)-[:HAS_COMPETITOR]->(o2:Organization) WHERE exists { ... duration > 10 years } RETURN o1.name AS org1, o2.name AS org2
typeql: match $o1 isa organization; $o2 isa organization; (competitor: $o1, competitor: $o2) isa competes_with; fetch { "org1": $o1.name, "org2": $o2.name };
review_reason: Missing time duration check: TypeQL does not filter by competition duration > 10 years

question: Name the organizations that are headquartered in cities known for their technology industry.
cypher: MATCH (o:Organization)-[:IN_CITY]->(c:City) WHERE c.name IN ['San Francisco', 'Seattle', ...] RETURN o.name AS organization, c.name AS city
typeql: match $o isa organization; $c isa city; (organization: $o, city: $c) isa located_in; fetch { "organization": $o.name, "city": $c.city_name };
review_reason: Missing city filter: TypeQL returns all organizations in any city, not just tech hub cities

question: List the cities that have organizations with a revenue exceeding 500 million.
cypher: MATCH (c:City)<-[:IN_CITY]-(o:Organization) WHERE o.revenue > 5e8 RETURN c.name AS city
typeql: match $c isa city; $o isa organization; (organization: $o, city: $c) isa located_in; $o has revenue $o_revenue; $o_revenue > 5; fetch { "city": $c.city_name };
review_reason: Wrong revenue threshold: TypeQL uses > 5 instead of > 500000000 (500 million)

question: Identify the organizations that have been dissolved but still mentioned in recent articles.
cypher: MATCH (o:Organization {isDissolved: true})<-[:MENTIONS]-(a:Article) WHERE a.date >= datetime() - duration('P1Y') RETURN o.name AS organization, a.title AS article, a.date ORDER BY a.date DESC
typeql: match $o isa organization, has is_dissolved true; $a isa article; (article: $a, organization: $o) isa mentions; $a has date $a_date; sort $a_date desc; fetch { "organization": $o.name, "article": $a.title, "date": $a.date };
review_reason: Missing recency filter: TypeQL does not filter articles to only those from the past year

question: List the articles that mention organizations headquartered in 'Seattle'.
cypher: MATCH (a:Article)-[:MENTIONS]->(o:Organization)-[:IN_CITY]->(:City {name: 'Seattle'}) RETURN a.title, a.summary, a.date, o.name
typeql: match $a isa article; $o isa organization; (article: $a, organization: $o) isa mentions; fetch { "title": $a.title, "article_summary": $a.article_summary, "date": $a.date, "name": $o.name };
review_reason: Missing Seattle city filter: TypeQL returns all articles mentioning any organization, not just those in Seattle

question: Name the industry categories for organizations that have been mentioned in articles about environmental issues.
cypher: MATCH (article:Article)-[:HAS_CHUNK]->(chunk:Chunk) WHERE toLower(chunk.text) CONTAINS 'environment' ... RETURN DISTINCT category.name
typeql: match $article isa article; $chunk isa chunk; (article: $article, chunk: $chunk) isa has_chunk; $org isa organization; $category isa industry_category; (article: $article, organization: $org) isa mentions; fetch { "industry_category_name": $category.industry_category_name };
review_reason: Missing environment text filter and org-category relation: TypeQL does not filter by 'environment' in chunk text and does not connect org to category

question: Which organizations have a CEO who is also an investor in other organizations?
cypher: MATCH (ceo:Person)<-[:HAS_CEO]-(org:Organization)-[:HAS_INVESTOR]->(investedOrg:Organization) WHERE (ceo)-[:HAS_INVESTOR]->(investedOrg) RETURN org.name AS organization, ceo.name AS ceo, investedOrg.name AS investedOrganization
typeql: match $ceo isa person; $org isa organization; $investedOrg isa organization; (organization: $org, ceo: $ceo) isa ceo_of; fetch { "organization": $org.name, "ceo": $ceo.name, "investedOrganization": $investedOrg.name };
review_reason: Missing CEO-investor relationship: TypeQL does not verify that the CEO is an investor in other organizations

question: List the organizations that have both a high revenue and a high number of employees.
cypher: MATCH (o:Organization) WHERE o.revenue > 1E8 AND o.nbrEmployees > 1000 ... ORDER BY o.revenue DESC, o.nbrEmployees DESC
typeql: match $o isa organization; $o has revenue $o_revenue; $o has nbr_employees $o_nbr_employees; $o_revenue > 1; $o_nbr_employees > 1000; sort $o_revenue desc; fetch { "organization": $o.name, "revenue": $o.revenue, "employees": $o.nbr_employees };
review_reason: Wrong revenue threshold: TypeQL uses > 1 instead of > 100000000 (100 million)

question: Which organizations are based in the same city as 'Accenture'?
cypher: MATCH (accenture:Organization {name: 'Accenture'})-[:IN_CITY]->(city:City)<-[:IN_CITY]-(other:Organization) WHERE other <> accenture RETURN other.name AS organization
typeql: match $accenture isa organization, has name "Accenture"; $city isa city; $other isa organization; (organization: $accenture, city: $city) isa located_in; fetch { "organization": $other.name };
review_reason: Missing other org location and inequality: TypeQL finds Accenture's city but does not connect other orgs to same city or exclude Accenture

question: Which organizations have a board member who is a CEO of a competitor organization?
cypher: MATCH (o1:Organization)-[:HAS_BOARD_MEMBER]->(p:Person)<-[:HAS_CEO]-(o2:Organization), (o1)-[:HAS_COMPETITOR]->(o2) RETURN ...
typeql: match $o1 isa organization; $p isa person; $o2 isa organization; (organization: $o1, member: $p) isa board_member_of; (competitor: $o1, competitor: $o2) isa competes_with; fetch { "Organization": $o1.name, "BoardMember": $p.name, "CompetitorWithBoardMemberAsCEO": $o2.name };
review_reason: Missing CEO relationship: TypeQL does not verify that the person is CEO of o2

question: List the organizations that have the most negative sentiment articles mentioning them.
cypher: MATCH (o:Organization)<-[:MENTIONS]-(a:Article) WITH o, avg(a.sentiment) AS avgSentiment ORDER BY avgSentiment ASC LIMIT 10 RETURN o.name AS organization, avgSentiment
typeql: match $o isa organization; $a isa article; (article: $a, organization: $o) isa mentions; limit 10; fetch { "organization": $o.name };
review_reason: Missing sentiment aggregation and sorting: TypeQL does not compute average sentiment or sort by it

question: List the cities where the most CEOs of large organizations reside.
cypher: MATCH (c:City)<-[:IN_CITY]-(o:Organization)-[:HAS_CEO]->(p:Person) WHERE o.nbrEmployees > 1000 RETURN c.name AS city, count(p) AS ceoCount ORDER BY ceoCount DESC LIMIT 10
typeql: match $c isa city; $o isa organization; $p isa person; (organization: $o, city: $c) isa located_in; $o has nbr_employees $o_nbr_employees; $o_nbr_employees > 1000; limit 10; reduce $ceoCount = count($p);
review_reason: Missing CEO relationship and proper grouping: TypeQL does not connect org to CEO and does not properly count/group by city

question: Which organizations have the most positive sentiment articles mentioning them?

typeql: match $o isa organization; $a isa article; (article: $a, organization: $o) isa mentions; limit 10; fetch { "organization": $o.name };
review_reason: Missing sentiment aggregation and sorting: TypeQL does not compute average sentiment or sort by it descending

question: List the organizations that have a subsidiary and a supplier in the same country.
cypher: MATCH (o:Organization)-[:HAS_SUBSIDIARY]->(sub:Organization), (o)-[:HAS_SUPPLIER]->(sup:Organization), (sub)-[:IN_CITY]->(:City)-[:IN_COUNTRY]->(c:Country), (sup)-[:IN_CITY]->(:City)-[:IN_COUNTRY]->(c) RETURN o.name AS organization, c.name AS country
typeql: match $o isa organization; $sub isa organization; $sup isa organization; $c isa country; (parent: $o, subsidiary: $sub) isa subsidiary_of; (customer: $o, supplier: $sup) isa supplies; fetch { "organization": $o.name, "country": $c.country_name };
review_reason: Missing location relationships: TypeQL does not verify subsidiary and supplier are in the same country via city-country chain

question: Identify the organizations that have been mentioned in the most articles about technology.
cypher: MATCH (o:Organization)<-[:MENTIONS]-(a:Article) WHERE (o)-[:HAS_CATEGORY]->(:IndustryCategory {name: 'Technology'}) WITH o, count(a) as mentionCount ORDER BY mentionCount DESC RETURN o.name as organization, mentionCount LIMIT 10
typeql: match $o isa organization; $a isa article; (article: $a, organization: $o) isa mentions; reduce $mentionCount = count($a) groupby $o; sort $mentionCount desc; limit 10; fetch { "organization": $o.name, "mentionCount": $mentionCount };
review_reason: Missing Technology category filter: TypeQL counts all articles, not just those about technology organizations

question: List the top 5 organizations by number of articles mentioning them.
cypher: MATCH (o:Organization)<-[:MENTIONS]-(a:Article) RETURN o.name AS organization, count(a) AS mentions ORDER BY mentions DESC LIMIT 5
typeql: match $o isa organization; $a isa article; (article: $a, organization: $o) isa mentions; limit 5; reduce $mentions = count($a);
review_reason: Wrong order of operations: TypeQL limits before counting, should count per org, sort, then limit

question: Identify the first 3 industries mentioned in articles written by David Correa.
cypher: MATCH (a:Article {author: 'David Correa'})-[:HAS_CHUNK]->(c:Chunk) MATCH (a)-[:MENTIONS]->(o:Organization)-[:HAS_CATEGORY]->(ic:IndustryCategory) RETURN ic.name AS industry ORDER BY a.date DESC LIMIT 3
typeql: match $a isa article, has author "David Correa"; $c isa chunk; (article: $a, chunk: $c) isa has_chunk; $o isa organization; $ic isa industry_category; (article: $a, organization: $o) isa mentions; $a has date $a_date; sort $a_date desc; limit 3; fetch { "industry": $ic.industry_category_name };

question: What are the names of the first 5 people who are board members of more than one organization?

question: Which organizations have subsidiaries within the same city?
cypher: MATCH (o:Organization)-[:HAS_SUBSIDIARY]->(sub:Organization), (o)-[:IN_CITY]->(c:City)<-[:IN_CITY]-(sub) RETURN o.name AS organization, sub.name AS subsidiary, c.name AS city
typeql: match $o isa organization; $sub isa organization; $c isa city; (parent: $o, subsidiary: $sub) isa subsidiary_of; (organization: $o, city: $c) isa located_in; fetch { "organization": $o.name, "subsidiary": $sub.name, "city": $c.city_name };
review_reason: Missing subsidiary-city relationship: TypeQL does not verify subsidiary is in same city as parent org

question: Provide the names of the first 5 organizations that have at least one subsidiary.
cypher: MATCH (o:Organization)-[:HAS_SUBSIDIARY]->(:Organization) RETURN o.name LIMIT 5
typeql: match $o isa organization; limit 5; fetch { "name": $o.name };
review_reason: Missing subsidiary relationship: TypeQL returns any 5 organizations, not those with subsidiaries

question: Who are the board members of the first 3 public organizations?
cypher: MATCH (o:Organization) WHERE o.isPublic = true ... MATCH (o)-[:HAS_BOARD_MEMBER]->(p:Person) RETURN o.name AS organization, collect(p.name) AS board_members
typeql: match $o isa organization; $p isa person; (organization: $o, member: $p) isa board_member_of; $o has is_public $o_is_public; $o has is_public true; $o has name $o_name; sort $o_name asc; limit 3; fetch { "organization": $o.name };
review_reason: Missing board member names in output: TypeQL does not fetch the board member names

question: List the first 3 organizations that are competitors within the same industry category.

typeql: match $o1 isa organization; $c isa industry_category; $o2 isa organization; (organization: $o1, category: $c) isa in_category; limit 3; fetch { "Org1": $o1.name, "Org2": $o2.name, "Category": $c.industry_category_name };
review_reason: Missing competitor and shared category checks: TypeQL does not verify orgs are competitors or that o2 shares the same category
